# Employees

## Overview

The Employees page allows authorised users to view, filter, and manage the employee records within their accessible companies.

## Access

| Role  | Access                                                |
| ----- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| Admin | Full access — can view employees across all companies |
| Owner | Access limited to their own companies                 |

All other roles are redirected away from this page.

## Company Filter

- **Admin** — a dropdown listing all companies is always visible and clearable (can reset to view all).
- **Owner** — a dropdown listing only the companies they own is shown when they own more than one company. If they own exactly one company it is auto-selected.

## Table Columns

| Column     | Description                                                                     |
| ---------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Full name  | First + last name of the employee                                               |
| Email      | Work email address                                                              |
| Employee # | Unique employee identifier                                                      |
| Department | Department the employee belongs to                                              |
| Position   | Job title / role                                                                |
| Status     | Employment status badge (`active`, `inactive`, `on_leave`, `terminated`)        |
| Managers   | Count badge — hover to see a tooltip listing all manager names                  |
| Managees   | Count badge — hover to see a tooltip listing all managee names                  |
| Actions    | **Deactivate** (sets status to `inactive`) · **Manage relations** (opens modal) |

## Actions

### Deactivate

Sets the employee's status to `inactive` via a PATCH request. Requires confirmation before applying.

### Manage Relations

Opens the **ManageRelationsModal** — a tabbed modal with two tabs:

- **Managers** — multi-select to assign which employees manage this person.
- **Managees** — multi-select to assign which employees this person manages.

Changes are saved in parallel and the list is invalidated on success.

## Adding a New Employee

The **New Employee** button is visible to Admins and Owners only. Clicking it opens the **CreateEmployeeModal** where the following fields are required:

- First name, Last name
- Email
- Employee number
- Hire date
- Position, Department
- Company (always required — selected from the accessible company list)

Optional fields: phone number, contract type, salary, hours per week.

A default password of `Password1!` is assigned on creation. The employee should change it on first login.

## Files

| File                       | Purpose                                                                 |
| -------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `Employees.tsx`            | Main page component — filter bar, AG Grid table, modal orchestration    |
| `Employees.columns.tsx`    | AG Grid column definitions including cell renderers and action handlers |
| `CreateEmployeeModal.tsx`  | Form modal for creating a new employee record                           |
| `ManageRelationsModal.tsx` | Tabbed modal for assigning managers and managees                        |
